### getToken
Use this method to get a specific token from our backend:
```
type Token = {
id: string;
created_at: string;
updated_at: string;
discarded_at: string | null;
endpoint?: string;
keys?: Record<string, string>;
};
await client.getToken(id: string): Promise<Token>
```
### getTokens
Use this method to get all webpush tokens for this user, from our backend:
```
type Token = {
id: string;
created_at: string;
updated_at: string;
discarded_at: string | null;
endpoint?: string;
keys?: Record<string, string>;
};
await client.getTokens(): Promise<Array<Token>>
```
### createToken
Use this method to create a webpush token in our backend.
Note:
`PushSubscriptionJSON` is a native web type, not exported from our packages.
```
